# Contributing to Order 66

Thank you for your interest in contributing to Order 66! Whether you're fixing bugs, improving documentation, enhancing the Sith-themed experience, or adding new features, your contributions are welcome.

## Ways to Contribute

* Fix bugs and improve performance.
* Add new productivity or gamification features.
* Improve UI/UX and accessibility.
* Enhance documentation.
* Write tests and improve code quality.
* Suggest ideas through issues and discussions.

## Getting Started

### 1. Fork the Repository

Create your own fork of the project.

### 2. Clone Your Fork

```bash
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/Order66.git
cd Order66
```

### 3. Create a Branch

```bash
git checkout -b feature/your-feature-name
```

## Development Guidelines

* Follow the existing project structure and coding style.
* Write clear and maintainable code.
* Keep pull requests focused on a single issue.
* Update documentation when necessary.
* Test your changes before submitting.

## Pull Request Process

Before opening a PR:

* Ensure your changes work as expected.
* Perform a self-review.
* Include screenshots for UI-related changes.
* Reference the related issue in your PR description.

### PR Title Examples

```text
feat: add Sith rank progression system
fix: resolve timer reset issue
docs: improve setup instructions
ui: enhance dashboard layout
```

## Issue Reporting

When creating an issue:

* Use a clear title.
* Describe the problem or suggestion.
* Include screenshots or reproduction steps when applicable.

## Community Support

If you enjoy the project and would like to support its growth, consider giving the repository a ⭐ star.

May your focus be strong and your streaks unbroken.
